<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-617-018  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 617 018.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  July 2 1990 n307 p12(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Who pays for fiber? (Metropolitan Fiber Systems Inc. charges BellRegional Holding Companies with cross-subsidization practices)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>In a filing with serious implications for telecommunicationscompetition, Metropolitan Fiber Systems charges that five BellRegional Holding Companies are improperly cross-subsidizing fiberoptic networks.andP;  The filing before the FCC contends that theRBOC's proposals to construct fiber optic networks in major citiesare being subsidized by local rate payers.andP;  The filing allegesthat the RBOCs are engaging in unfair competitive practices byraising millions from regulated local monopolies to develop fiberloops for larger users.andP;  The filing also contends that MFSnetworks should have the same interconnection rights to RBOC fibernetworks as the regionals themselves.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metropolitan Fiber Systems Inc. (cases).andO;Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesFiber OpticsCompetitionUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionLegal IssuesNetworksFunding.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>